        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37923",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan.stubbe",
                        "name": "stefan.stubbe",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Stubbe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To provide some more information, my current setup:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\/local\/www\/library\/My\r\n`-- Tool\r\n    |-- HelloProvider.php\r\n    `-- Manifest.php\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nMy\/Tool\/Manifest.php:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<?php\r\n\r\nclass My_Tool_Manifest implements Zend_Tool_Framework_Manifest_ProviderManifestable\r\n{\r\n        public function getProviders()\r\n        {\r\n                return array(\r\n                        new My_Tool_HelloProvider\r\n                );\r\n        }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nMy\/Tool\/HelloProvider.php\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<?php\r\n\r\nclass My_Tool_HelloProvider implements Zend_Tool_Framework_Provider_Interface\r\n{\r\n        public function say()\r\n        {\r\n                echo 'Hello from my provider!', PHP_EOL;\r\n        }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nCommand I am using:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\/home\/yahiko $ cd \/local\/www\/library\r\n\/local\/www\/library $ ZEND_TOOL_INCLUDE_PATH=$(pwd) \/local\/www\/library\/ZendFramework-1.10.0rc1-minimal\/bin\/zf.sh say hello\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan.stubbe",
                        "name": "stefan.stubbe",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Stubbe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-22T01:42:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-22T01:42:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37935",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The include path loader has been replaced with the basic loader.\r\n\r\nYou have to hook custom classes into Zend Tool by adding the following line to your .zf.ini:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nbasicloader.classes.0 = \"My_ClassName\"\r\nbasicloader.classes.1 = \"My_Manifest\"\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nOr you use the command:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nbenny@benny-pc:~$ zf enable config.?\r\nZend Framework Command Line Console Tool v1.10.0alpha\r\nDetails for action \"Enable\" and provider \"Config\"\r\n    zf enable config.manifest class-name\r\n    zf enable config.provider class-name\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis does the same.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-22T05:16:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-22T05:16:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37941",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan.stubbe",
                        "name": "stefan.stubbe",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Stubbe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Adding the custom classes to my .zf.ini did the trick.\r\n\r\nThe [documentation|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/1.10\/en\/zend.tool.extending.html#zend.tool.extending.zend-tool-framework.providers-and-manifests.loading] however does not mention this and still talks about the IncludePathLoader\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan.stubbe",
                        "name": "stefan.stubbe",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Stubbe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-22T06:58:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-22T06:58:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39157",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guille",
                        "name": "guille",
                        "displayName": "Guillermo Thiemann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would say that the environment-level configuration .zf.ini is a bad location to put custom providers anyway.\r\n\r\nWhat if I have project-specific Providers and more than one Project running in one server?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guille",
                        "name": "guille",
                        "displayName": "Guillermo Thiemann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-11T02:23:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-11T02:23:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39493",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jstuart",
                        "name": "jstuart",
                        "displayName": "James Stuart",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree. Causing Zend Tool extensions to be loaded globally (per user) significantly diminishes their usefulness for project based tasks.\r\n\r\nWe have many developers, each with multiple workstations, working on many projects.  Having your configuration based on the user account (and workstation) that you're using and not the application that you're working on is a hurdle that will prevent us from using Zend Tool at all.\r\n\r\nOn the server side, our hosting setup causes us to have many applications on the same server running as the same user.  We obviously cannot use the same configuration for each application, so the environment-level configuration doesn't work here either.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jstuart",
                        "name": "jstuart",
                        "displayName": "James Stuart",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-23T12:54:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-23T12:54:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42639",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
